===message:The rise of communism were the causes of anti-communism hysteria. The Soviet-controlled communist government were formed in most countries of Eastern Europe. As well as, Germany communist controlled East Germany. Chinese Government established the People's Republic of China. Other Asian nation also came under communist control. Communism appeared to be an epidemic. Alarmed by communist expansion, the United States and it's allies began giving military and economic aid to non-communist countries and pledge to help nations threatened by communist take-over. McCarthyism was supported greatly because the American people still had a distrust in the government. The 911 incident terrorize most Americans to believe that we are not safe in our own country. Because we are considered a super-power, we never had to worry about fighting a war on our own turf. 911 helped us the realize that we are not exempt from terrorists attacks. As a precaution, Americans have purchase duct tape and plastic sheeting to protect themselves from chemical and biological weapons.  
=========yorg=========
===from:Lorena Lockhart
===date:Sat Mar 22 20:46:08 2003
===subject:Chap. 8
===message:The anticommunist hysteria had its beginnings with the establishment of the House Un-American Activities Committee in 1938. Truman's Executive Order 9835 brought further unrest. This order established the Federal Employee Loyalty Program. Although geared towards loyalty checks on government employees, it soon spread to all other areas of the American work force, including schoolteachers and college professors. While there was good reason for concern and some sort of safeguards needed to be in place, the Federal Employee Loyalty Program had weak measures to insure civil rights. This gave way to what I am sure were many injustices that were served during this time of paranoia by the American people. Some accusation and treats were made and lives ruined based on nothing but their association with others. The Hollywood 10 were sent to federal prison simply because they did not cooperate. Was any evidence of wrongdoing brought against them? Others were outcast simply because they were Jews. The Dennis v. US decision threatened freedom of speech. Then, in an effort for political gain, McCarthy began his attacks on elected officials. He received encouragement from other 
Republicans strictly for the purpose of winning the 1952 election for the Republican party. Had Truman's political views been more popular, McCarthy probably would not have been able to gain the support that he did. To many Republicans, anticommunist was a weapon against the Democrats. American is prone to panic just as any other country is prone to panic. It is the human instinct for self-preservation. In relating to 9/11 Americans are not the only ones who have been placed on alert. The entire world with the exception of terrorists supporters, has responded with fear of who might be living next door, who might work in your building with you, who might work in the post office, who is flying the plane. This list goes on and on and no matter how much duck tape or plastic sheeting is used nothing can stop what is already written. 
=========yorg=========
===from:James Pike
===date:Sun Mar 23 13:30:18 2003
===subject:Chapter 8
===message:The causes of anticommunist hysteria that swept the United States began as a result of the American public’s fear of the atomic bomb.  Americans feared the destructive nature of the atomic bomb, but more so, they feared that the power and devastation of this bomb was now in the hands of another country.  Furthermore, the fact that they no longer had the monopoly on the atomic bomb and later the hydrogen bomb, made America equal in world matters- no longer could America yield the destructive might they once solely possessed.  America once again had to compromise.  McCarthyism received so much support for two reasons.  The first reason lies in the inability for the American public to rationally think through things at times.  Americans were scared of what they had no control over, thus they followed whomever they felt could gain control.  The second reason for the acceptance of McCarthyism and probably the true reason that it received so much support were because of the power that it had and the injustice that it served.  Many people were scared of not being supportive of McCarthyism.  After all, those who did not support McCarthyism’s removal of communism must be communist themselves.  Americans are prone to panic when they are taken out of their comfort zone.  We do not know how to react when things do not always go our way.  This relates to the events of 9-11 because it took us out of our comfort zones.  The duct tape and plastic sheeting are ways to make ourselves comfortable that we cannot be harmed.  
=========yorg=========
