===message:The Soviet Union's atomic bombing began the anticommunist hysteria, which changed the world.  McCarthyism recieved so much support because it actually caused the nation to think the way they did, and they were actually interested.  I think the government plays a big part as to why Americans are prone to panic.  The government is able to manipulate a lot of people into thinking certain problems that are occuring around the world will harm them unless if they did certain things to prevent it from happening.  I see it like this, there is no need for me to take "out of the ordinary" precautions, because there is always another way terrorists could have an attack, that the government may not even think of.  Why stress it?
