===subject:Diss 8
===message:The causes of anticommunism hysteria that swept that nation during the 1940’s and 1950’s was the Cold War evolving, the Red Scare of World War II, the establishment of the House Committee on Un-American Activities. The reason why McCarthyism received so much support is because he informed his fellow Republicans that the Democrats were being too easy on the communists. When he filed a suit against several women he thought were communists after attending a GOP meeting West Virginia, his effort to prove that communism existed in the GOP, gained support of many Americans. Americans are so prone to panic because we live in a country where our government is unjust and dishonest and a time where the possibility of any type of threat on our soil is unimagined and unrealized. The Civil War and the Pearl Harbor attacks are the last major incidents on our soil the effects of both have been long forgotten by the average American. Americans are so prone to panic because of the guilt that many like to hide but carry it inside.  Many I know feel that 9/11 happened because of some covert attempt or success by the US in a foreighn country. This is why such panic arose when the September 11th attacks happened.  Many Americans feel that we are getting paid back for the attrocities we have dished out or allowed to happen over time. The government is probably the most active propoganda machine every created.  Because of our so called humanitarian concerns we cloak our real reasons for what we do or why we do. When the government informed the public of the possible threat of biological weapons from terrorists and made suggestions to prevent infection, Americans bought massive quantities of duct tape and plastic sheeting.  Now seriously do you really think this will protect you from Biological weapons! :) 

=========yorg=========
===from:Bethany Ballard
