===subject:chapter 8
===message:The causes of the hysteria were the Cold War, the Red Scare and the investigations of the HUAC.  America was so afraid of the communists taking over, and they were paranoid that communists were among them.  McCarthyism was so popular because Joe McCarthy revealed to America how the democrats were "soft on communism."  America wanted someone who would stand against communism which is what made him so popular.  I think Americans are so prone to panic because of the fear that the media puts into their minds.  Since September 11th, everyone is afraid of another attack and now of nuclear warfare.  The media is suggesting people to go out and buy duct tape and plastic sheeting to help protect against nuclear warfare, which has many people in a panic.  

